NYON Manchester United were charged by Uefa on Wednesday for a pitch invasion at Old Trafford during their Champions League defeat by Juventus. Three fans managed to get past the stewards early in Tuesday's game, with one, who was wearing a United shirt, appearing to try and touch Cristiano Ronaldo as the Juventus forward returned to his former club. Uefa also fined the three-time European champions after their draw with Valencia earlier this month for a delayed kick-off and for arriving late to the stadium.Jose Mourinho's United slumped to a 1-0 loss as Paulo Dybala scored for Juve, who lead Group H from the English giants by five points.   Ronaldo did not get on the scoresheet.